To scale down the RabbitMQ cluster just perform a normal upgrade setting the *replicaCount* value to the desired number of nodes. For example, reduce the cluster to one replica (default number):

~~~
$ helm upgrade bitnami/rabbitmq \
--set password=RABBITMQ_PASSWORD \
--set replicaCount=1 \
--set auth.erlangCookie=RABBITMQ_ERLANG_COOKIE
~~~

> NOTE: You need to replace the RABBITMQ_PASSWORD and RABBITMQ_ERLANG_COOKIE placeholders with the values obtained in the installation notes.
